[Insurance related medical aspects of angina pectoris].

[Article in German]

Grond A(1).

Author information:
(1)Kölnischen Rückversicherungs-Gesellschaft.

Angina pectoris or chest pain is the main symptom of coronary insufficiency 
which may lead to reversible or irreversible ischaemia. It must be distinguished 
from other cardiac or thoracic causes. Nervous or functional disorders hardly 
influence life expectancy. Unstable angina pectoris, pre-infarction syndrome or 
post-infarction angina cannot be accepted for life insurance. We have divided 
stable angina pectoris into four classes in accordance with the NYHA 
classification. We have indicated the relevant extra mortality. Separate 
consideration must be given to additional factors adversely affecting the risk.

