Changes in timing of fertility--a Canadian experience.

Rajulton F(1), Balakrishnan TR, Chen JJ.

Author information:
(1)Department of Sociology, University of Western Ontario, London, Canada.

This paper examines the patterns of timing of births of women using data from 
the Canadian Fertility Survey of 1984. Semi-Markovian schemes are applied to the 
maternity histories of the 5315 sample women in their reproductive ages in order 
