To identify patients undergoing carotid endarterectomy who are at high risk for 
cardiac events and death, we studied the course of 614 patients with known risk 
factors who were entered into our carotid follow-up registry. Patients were 
divided into two groups, group I with overt coronary disease (prior myocardial 
infarction, angina, significant electrocardiographic abnormalities) (N = 324) 
